sentences: Erik Hillestad (born 12 December 1951) is a Norwegian record producer and lyricist.
He has received several awards for his works, including a 1992 Fritt Ord Honorary Award.
He married Marianne Lystrup in 1971, and is a brother-in-law of Geirr Lystrup.
Hillestad established in 1974 the record company Kirkelig Kulturverksted, for which he has produced a large part of the releases.
